Overview[edit]




Thapana Sirivadhanabhakdi, company president and CEO


Thai Beverage Public Company Limited owns and distributes several significant brands, including Chang beer, Mekhongand SangSom rum. It also has significant operations in Europe, producing malt Scotch whisky, vodka, gin, and liqueurs with over 20 distilleries in Scotland, France, Poland, and Ireland. Mr Charoen Sirivadhanabhakdi in early 2013, added Fraser and Neave, Limited, a food and beverage, brewing, property, and publishing industries conglomerate in Singapore, to his drinks and property empire.[4]
